### 1.2 Port Conflict Analysis

✅ **No Port Conflicts Detected**

- All services use unique port assignments
- Internal container ports (8000) are properly mapped to unique external ports (8011-8018)
- Database services (PostgreSQL:5432, Redis:6379) are isolated to Docker network only
- No overlap between monitoring (9090, 9093, 3000) and application services

### 1.3 Firewall Requirements

#### Production Firewall Rules

```
INBOUND RULES:
- ALLOW TCP 443 (HTTPS) from 0.0.0.0/0 → Ingress Controller
- ALLOW TCP 80 (HTTP) from 0.0.0.0/0 → Ingress Controller (redirect to HTTPS)
- ALLOW TCP 6443 (Kubernetes API) from Trusted Admin IPs
- DENY ALL other inbound traffic

OUTBOUND RULES:
- ALLOW TCP 443 (HTTPS) to 0.0.0.0/0 (External APIs)
- ALLOW UDP 53 (DNS) to Internal DNS Servers
- DENY TCP 5432 (PostgreSQL) to external networks
- DENY TCP 6379 (Redis) to external networks
- ALLOW TCP 7233 (Temporal) within cluster network only

INTERNAL RULES (Kubernetes NetworkPolicy):
- Default DENY all ingress/egress
- Explicit ALLOW policies per namespace (see NetworkPolicy section)
```

