## 3. Network Security Assessment

### 3.1 Zero-Trust Architecture Implementation

✅ **Implemented**: Default Deny + Explicit Allow

```yaml
Zero-Trust Enforcement Layers:

Layer 1: Namespace Isolation
  - 6 isolated namespaces (core, eca, security, monitoring, memory, production)
  - Default deny all ingress/egress per namespace
  - Explicit allow policies required

Layer 2: Network Policies
  - 15+ NetworkPolicy resources deployed
  - Pod-level traffic filtering
  - Label-based policy application

Layer 3: RBAC
  - ServiceAccount per deployment
  - Least-privilege access model
  - Role-based policy enforcement

Layer 4: Security Contexts
  - runAsNonRoot: true (all pods)
  - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
  - Capabilities dropped (ALL)
  - seccompProfile: RuntimeDefault

Layer 5: Ingress Security
  - Rate limiting (100 req/s)
  - Request validation
  - TLS enforcement
  - Security headers
```

### 3.2 Network Policies (Kubernetes)

#### Default Deny Policies

```yaml
Namespaces with Default Deny:
✅ project-ai-production
✅ project-ai-staging
✅ project-ai-core
✅ project-ai-security
✅ project-ai-memory
✅ project-ai-eca (Maximum Isolation)
✅ kyverno

Policy: Deny all ingress and egress by default
Enforcement: Immediate upon namespace creation
```

#### Explicit Allow Policies

**ECA Namespace (Maximum Isolation)**
```yaml
Ingress: DENIED (no inbound traffic allowed)
Egress:
  - DNS resolution (UDP/TCP 53)
  - HTTPS to external APIs only (TCP 443)
  - NO internal cluster communication
  - NO cross-namespace access

Purpose: External Cognition Amplifier isolation
Threat Model: Prevent lateral movement from compromised ECA
```

**Core Namespace (Standard Isolation)**
```yaml
Ingress:
  - From ingress-nginx namespace (port 8080)
  - From monitoring namespace (port 9090)
  - From pods in same namespace

Egress:
  - DNS resolution
  - To memory namespace (PostgreSQL 5432)
  - To external HTTPS (443, 80)
  
Purpose: Main application services
```

**Security Namespace (High Isolation)**
```yaml
Ingress:
  - From monitoring namespace ONLY

Egress:
  - DNS resolution
  - Read-only access to all namespaces (ports 8080, 9090)
  - NO write access to any service

Purpose: Cerberus security monitoring
Threat Model: Read-only observer, cannot modify resources
```

**Monitoring Namespace (Observability)**
```yaml
Ingress:
  - From ingress-nginx (Grafana UI: 3000, Prometheus: 9090)
  - From all project-ai namespaces (metrics push)

Egress:
  - DNS resolution
  - Scrape metrics from all namespaces (8080, 9090)
  - External alerting (HTTPS 443)

Purpose: Metrics collection and visualization
```

**Memory Namespace (Database)**
```yaml
Ingress:
  - From core namespace (PostgreSQL 5432)
  - From monitoring namespace

Egress:
  - DNS resolution
  - Pod-to-pod (database replication)

Purpose: Persistent data storage
Threat Model: Database isolation from external access
```

### 3.3 mTLS Between Services

⚠️ **Not Implemented** - Recommendation for Enhancement

**Current State:**
- No service mesh (Istio/Linkerd) deployed
- Internal traffic is HTTP (not HTTPS)
- TLS termination at Ingress Controller only

**Recommendation:**
```yaml
Service Mesh Implementation (Istio):

Benefits:
  - Automatic mTLS between all services
  - Zero-trust at network layer
  - Traffic encryption in transit
  - Certificate rotation (every 24h)
  - Mutual authentication

Implementation:
  1. Deploy Istio control plane
  2. Enable auto-injection: istio-injection=enabled
  3. Configure PeerAuthentication (STRICT mTLS)
  4. Verify with: istioctl authn tls-check

Estimated Impact:
  - Security Score: +15 points
  - Latency: +2-5ms (acceptable for security)
  - CPU: +10% (sidecar overhead)
```

### 3.4 Firewall & Security Groups

#### Cloud Provider Security Groups (AWS/GCP/Azure)

```yaml
Security Group: project-ai-cluster

Inbound Rules:
  1. HTTPS (443) from 0.0.0.0/0 → Load Balancer
  2. HTTP (80) from 0.0.0.0/0 → Load Balancer (redirect)
  3. Kubernetes API (6443) from Admin VPN (10.0.1.0/24)
  4. SSH (22) from Bastion Host (10.0.0.10/32)
  5. DENY ALL others

Outbound Rules:
  1. HTTPS (443) to 0.0.0.0/0 (External APIs)
  2. DNS (53) to VPC DNS (10.0.0.2)
  3. PostgreSQL (5432) within VPC only
  4. Redis (6379) within VPC only
  5. DENY RFC1918 ranges from egressing to internet

Security Group: project-ai-db

Inbound Rules:
  1. PostgreSQL (5432) from project-ai-cluster SG
  2. DENY ALL others

Outbound Rules:
  1. PostgreSQL (5432) within DB subnet (replication)
  2. DENY ALL others
```

### 3.5 DDoS Protection & Rate Limiting

```yaml
Layer 7 Rate Limiting (NGINX Ingress):
  - Requests per second: 100
  - Concurrent connections: 10 per IP
  - Burst: 20 requests
  - Response: 429 Too Many Requests
  - Enforcement: Per client IP address

Layer 4 Rate Limiting (Cloud Provider):
  - AWS Shield Standard (free DDoS protection)
  - AWS WAF (optional): $5/month + $1/million requests
  - GCP Cloud Armor: DDoS protection + WAF rules
  - Azure DDoS Protection Standard

Application-Level Rate Limiting:
  Location: API Gateway (port 8001)
  Implementation: Token bucket algorithm
  Limits:
    - Unauthenticated: 60 req/min
    - Authenticated: 120 req/min (staging), 60 req/min (production)
    - Admin: 300 req/min

Circuit Breaker Pattern:
  Status: ✅ Implemented
  Failure Threshold: 5 consecutive failures
  Timeout: 30 seconds
  Half-Open State: Test with 1 request
  Reset: After 3 successful requests
```

